Dialogue: 2,0:02:16.57,0:02:22.58,Mushisode Title,,0,0,0,eptitle,{\fad(2000,0)\an4\blur0.6\pos(280,108)}Lightning's End
Dialogue: 10,0:02:43.36,0:02:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:45.25,0:02:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother, I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:54.33,0:02:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:56.78,0:02:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm scared!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:58.23,0:02:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Please help me!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:01.44,0:03:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:18.40,0:03:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:22.83,0:03:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That must be it.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:27.12,0:03:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Is something wrong with that tree?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:31.00,0:03:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard it's been struck by lightning multiple times.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:33.60,0:03:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It must trouble you and your family.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:36.75,0:03:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought there may be an underlying cause.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:42.65,0:03:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of a cause?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:45.16,0:03:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Although that tree is magnificent,
Dialogue: 10,0:03:47.47,0:03:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,there are other large trees in its vicinity.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:50.96,0:03:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, it's possible that it's been struck by lightning so many times
Dialogue: 10,0:03:54.35,0:03:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,because other factors are involved.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:59.64,0:04:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, it may be inhabited by a mushi.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:04.78,0:04:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,A mushi?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:06.19,0:04:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:07.44,0:04:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I am Ginko, a mushi-shi.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:11.02,0:04:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So would it be possible for me \Nto see the tree in your backyard?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:18.20,0:04:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Please wait here.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:20.89,0:04:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I must ask my husband first.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:30.19,0:04:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Seems there aren't any in this tree.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:32.92,0:04:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If that's the case...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:34.75,0:04:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,has anyone in your household been struck by lightning?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:48.43,0:04:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Come in, Reki.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:58.65,0:05:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then, would you mind showing me your abdomen?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:07.77,0:05:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There it is.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:10.35,0:05:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Whenever there's thunder and lightning,
Dialogue: 10,0:05:11.94,0:05:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,does it start to feel hot around your navel?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:17.92,0:05:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,How long ago was he hit by lightning?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:20.62,0:05:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The first time was five years ago,
Dialogue: 10,0:05:23.23,0:05:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,under that tree.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:26.24,0:05:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Since then, he's been hit about three more times...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:29.61,0:05:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,all while he was under that tree.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:34.33,0:05:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a miracle he survived.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:36.43,0:05:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:38.73,0:05:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:41.39,0:05:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,As I suspected, the cause is a mushi.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:45.51,0:05:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It is?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:48.45,0:05:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a Shouraishi, \Nor "Lightning Summoner" mushi.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:51.05,0:05:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Typically, it hovers in the sky \Nand eats lightning to sustain itself.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:56.41,0:06:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,However, its larvae sometimes fall \Nto the surface when lightning strikes.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:05.24,0:06:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,After a Shouraishi larva falls, \Nit is unable to return to the sky on its own.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:09.50,0:06:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It may therefore hide in a nearby tree hollow,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:12.28,0:06:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,or if a person is nearby,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:13.78,0:06:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,it may enter his body through the navel \Nand hide there instead.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:17.44,0:06:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,While it remains in its host's body,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:19.57,0:06:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,it discharges electricity \Nand calls lightning down to it.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:22.97,0:06:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It does so in order to eat the lightning and eventually emerge as an adult.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:26.72,0:06:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:29.21,0:06:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Since the Shouraishi eats lightning,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:31.85,0:06:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the host may be struck by lightning, \Nbut he does not usually die as a result.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:37.29,0:06:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,However, if it continues to happen,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:39.36,0:06:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,it will eventually prove fatal.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:42.97,0:06:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,When there is lightning, it would be best if he hid in a nearby cave of some sort.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:47.72,0:06:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I often tell him to go into the cellar,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:50.72,0:06:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,but he refuses to listen.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:55.48,0:06:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, there are ways to extract the Shouraishi from him.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:59.13,0:07:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We would simply need to make \Nan infusion out of his umbilical cord.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:03.55,0:07:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's all right, may we use it to help him?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:07.13,0:07:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, but I'm not quite sure where I put it...
Dialogue: 10,0:07:11.44,0:07:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Shino!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:12.60,0:07:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you always like this?!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:15.26,0:07:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Reki's life we're talking about here!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:17.56,0:07:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Find it immediately!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:20.52,0:07:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay—
Dialogue: 10,0:07:20.93,0:07:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:24.22,0:07:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't mind it.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:40.99,0:07:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Reki, please return to your room for now.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:49.85,0:07:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry about that.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:53.05,0:07:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm certain she has it somewhere around here.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:55.36,0:07:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you wait here for her?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:58.60,0:08:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then, I must get back to work myself.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:03.76,0:08:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's not too rude, I'd like to ask a personal question.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:08.30,0:08:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Are your wife and son related by blood?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:12.04,0:08:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:16.41,0:08:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,My wife seems to struggle \Nwith how to relate to our son.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:22.89,0:08:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,However, she {\i1}did{\i0} give birth to him.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:46.57,0:08:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:48.68,0:08:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:52.76,0:08:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Please help me!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:55.04,0:08:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to go through \Nwith this arranged marriage.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:00.35,0:09:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,There's someone else I wish to marry!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:05.80,0:09:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:08.56,0:09:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:28.60,0:09:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Shino!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:35.99,0:09:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the meaning of this?!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:41.38,0:09:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to have this child.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:50.54,0:09:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:54.47,0:09:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure I won't love him.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:47.66,0:10:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Come inside.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:53.37,0:10:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not safe up there.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:01.11,0:11:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Reki?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:35.93,0:11:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you looking at?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:44.17,0:11:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The clouds.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:46.34,0:11:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,How's it look?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:47.47,0:11:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think any of them are thunder clouds?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:51.48,0:11:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Nah...
Dialogue: 10,0:11:54.09,0:11:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you're right.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:55.90,0:11:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine weather.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:59.59,0:12:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So,{for emphasis} are you always on the lookout for thunder clouds?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:05.08,0:12:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:08.14,0:12:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, why don't you ever try to run away from the lightning?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:10.90,0:12:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you scared?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:15.51,0:12:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I am.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:19.29,0:12:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But I like it.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:22.97,0:12:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's strong, and it's beautiful too.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:28.54,0:12:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither Father nor Mother look me in the eye.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:36.66,0:12:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But the lightning does. It always comes right for me.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:44.23,0:12:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, you can't predict the time when it might kill you.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:50.82,0:12:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:54.10,0:12:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It would have been better \Nif I'd never been born anyway.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:14.94,0:13:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you find it?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:18.33,0:13:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nowhere to be found...
Dialogue: 10,0:13:22.94,0:13:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I must have been careless and thrown it away somehow.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:29.02,0:13:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,There are other means.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:31.78,0:13:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We can even open him up to remove it.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:34.58,0:13:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,However, I'm not certain \Nyour son will allow us to do that.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:43.78,0:13:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because he's angry at his mother... \Nfor being this way.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:54.70,0:13:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why he has lightning strike right in front of me...
Dialogue: 10,0:13:58.04,0:13:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,He is punishing me.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:05.21,0:14:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And why shouldn't he?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:07.86,0:14:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm his mother,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:09.84,0:14:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet I haven't shown him any real affection.{i joe. no, he totsu}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:15.56,0:14:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Still,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:17.21,0:14:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I just don't know how
Dialogue: 10,0:14:20.09,0:14:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,to love him.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:31.08,0:14:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder what's going on here.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:33.83,0:14:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He is punishing me.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:37.90,0:14:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Is that really what he's doing?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:41.61,0:14:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Is that really why he sits up there, \Non that tree, and calls lightning down to himself?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:50.14,0:14:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, buddy!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:52.68,0:14:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You should stay away from that tree!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:55.54,0:14:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It attracts lightning!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:58.57,0:14:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:59.52,0:15:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:00.97,0:15:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's sunny, so it should be fine, \Ndon't you think?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:04.09,0:15:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The clouds are already forming, though.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:06.86,0:15:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Clouds around here get huge in no time.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:10.17,0:15:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So just be careful.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:12.14,0:15:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, let's get going.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:13.94,0:15:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:15.74,0:15:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Knock on wood.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:30.71,0:15:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,This is...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:01.90,0:16:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever asked him why he waits for the lightning
Dialogue: 10,0:16:06.25,0:16:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,specifically on top of that tree?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:12.22,0:16:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I already know the answer.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:16.62,0:16:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,There's another possible explanation.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:20.04,0:16:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}That tree, specifically, poses the lowest risk \Nof others' being harmed by the lightning that strikes him.{and yes, this apostrophe is correct. http://www.quickanddirtytips.com/education/grammar/do-i-hate-your-singing-or-you-singing}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:27.93,0:16:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It is also relatively far from your home,
Dialogue: 10,0:16:30.06,0:16:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,so the house is always safe from the lightning.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:35.13,0:16:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time, however,
Dialogue: 10,0:16:37.29,0:16:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,it's close enough for him to rush to \Nas soon as he notices lightning approaching.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:43.03,0:16:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, whenever the villagers hear thunder,
Dialogue: 10,0:16:44.85,0:16:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,they know to stay away from that tree.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:52.89,0:16:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You're saying...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:54.68,0:16:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,you never once considered that possibility?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:10.92,0:17:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He still hasn't gotten back yet.{"still" plus "yet" implies that he may have thought to himself sooner that the boy hadn't gotten home yet.}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:15.96,0:17:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have any idea where he might have gone?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:19.30,0:17:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:22.01,0:17:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,He may intend to call the lightning down elsewhere so that I cannot interfere.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:28.12,0:17:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Are there any other places \Nwhere it may be easy for him to do so?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:31.30,0:17:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,An open area with few people, for instance.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:36.23,0:17:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a meadow on the outskirts of the village.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:39.02,0:17:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:39.97,0:17:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to stop him.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:43.27,0:17:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:44.50,0:17:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to come too.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:47.61,0:17:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,He wouldn't listen to me anyway.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:51.62,0:17:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the only one who can stop him.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:54.73,0:17:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It {\i1}has{\i0} to be you.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:24.33,0:18:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Come back.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:32.95,0:18:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:36.18,0:18:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You might die.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:40.87,0:18:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:52.80,0:18:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, you've got to be more direct with him!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:56.55,0:18:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell him that you want him to live!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:18.68,0:19:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:22.87,0:19:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what,
Dialogue: 10,0:19:25.34,0:19:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't bring myself to think that way.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:45.51,0:19:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother—
Dialogue: 10,0:19:46.16,0:19:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 10,0:19:48.22,0:19:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's die together, then.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:55.10,0:19:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,In my next life,
Dialogue: 10,0:19:58.54,0:20:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure I'll be born as a mother who can properly love her child.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:33.98,0:20:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,He protected you.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:37.26,0:20:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:40.71,0:20:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet you still...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:47.05,0:20:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:27.58,0:21:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}After that,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:30.46,0:21:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}their son was taken in by a relative.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:37.40,0:21:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Perhaps that was the path this particular mother and her child had to take.
